From df3164284bcbee4a5615928f66893022859e2981 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sun, 31 May 2026 03:25:07 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix bugs, security issues, and missing features across
 backend and frontend
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Backend:
- Add JWT auth middleware and apply it to all protected routes (dashboard,
  transactions, upload, categories, accounts, ai). Auth routes remain public.
- Fix transactions COUNT query to apply the same WHERE filters as the
  paginated query so totals are accurate when filtering.
- Add limit/offset bounds validation (limit clamped 1–1000, offset >= 0).
- Add bulk-categorize input validation (non-empty array, positive integer IDs).
- Add category name validation (required, max 100 chars).
- Add month (1–12) and year (2000–2100) validation to AI summary route.
- Add CSV file type validation on upload (extension + MIME check).
- Fix csvParser date validation: parseDate returns null on invalid dates and
  all three parsers skip rows with unparseable dates instead of inserting
  Invalid Date into the database.
- Make CORS origin configurable via CORS_ORIGIN env var.

Frontend:
- Fix XSS in DashboardPage: sanitize AI summary text (escape HTML entities)
  before converting **bold** markdown to <strong> tags.
- Add error state display to DashboardPage (load error + AI summary error).
- Fix "Forgot password?" dead link in LoginPage: shows a Quasar notification
  instead of being a non-functional element.
- Add user-facing error banner to TransactionsPage on fetch failure.
- Add proper pagination to TransactionsPage (prev/next buttons, page X of Y,
  50 rows per page with offset tracking). Filters and search reset to page 1.
